title: Want To Buy:  Looking to purchase a Glock 19 or Glock 26
postcontent:
I am looking to buy a glock 19 or glock 26. I'll pay $525 for gen 3's and $600 for gen 4's. I am 18, and yes, it is completely legal for an 18-20 year old to purchase a handgun through a private party sale.

http://myfreedomfoundation.com/blog/liberty-live/detail/can-individuals-between-18-and-20-purchase-and-own-handguns> 

O.C.G.A. § 16-11-132
 Possession of a handgun by a person under the age of 18 years

 Georgia law only covers possession of handguns by those 
 "Under" the age of 18 with varying circumstances, as well as those 21+. That means a  person 18-20 can legally "posses" a handgun.


 O.C.G.A. § 16-11-101.1
 Furnishing pistol or revolver to person under the age of 18 years

 This law relates to the sale of handguns in Georgia through a private party (you and I) sale. Once again, it only refers to those "under" the age of 18. The rest of the laws that apply to the sale of handguns and handgun ammunition in Georgia are federal laws which only apply to an FFL or manufacturer. (http://www.nraila.org/gun-laws/articles/2004/citizen%60s-guide-to-federal-firearms-law.aspx> 

 O.C.G.A. § 16-11-126
 Having or carrying handguns, long guns, or other weapons; license requirement; exceptions for homes, motor vehicles, and other locations and conditions; penalties for violations

 A person of age 18-20 is treated as an adult who does not have a Georgia Weapons Carry License, and must abide by those same rules. Those rules, in short, mean that the handgun may not leave the confines of my home (property of said home included), motor vehicle, and/or place of business.

 I looked at some of the ar style .22 rifles and have to say this one was in my opinion the best. The weight is substantial. Hold this in one hand and the Mossberg or Colt version in the other and you will see what I mean. This is metal and solid. A great trainer.

 From Manufacturer:
 The .22 caliber HK 416 is loaded with authentic features. From its appearance, feel, and operation, right down to the sling swivel incorporated into the stock, the 416 D145RS is a replica in every sense.

 Like all the .22 LR H&K's, the 416 is a dedicated .22 rimfire rifle. It is engineered and built in Germany by Carl Walther with a match grade precision barrel, upper and lower metal receivers, a retractable stock, and a machined rail interface system. The 416’s pistol grip and buttstock are authentic in that they include storage compartments for small tools or batteries.

 The magazines for the .22 caliber 416 are made of high-strength polymer and are designed to make loading simple and efficient. They’re available in either a 20- or 10-round version. 

 The .22 caliber HK 416 D145RS operates on a blowback system. The dust cover functions and the bolt holds open when the magazine empties. Its sights are on-rail and the rear sight is adjustable for windage and elevation. Its safety selector rotates 90 degrees from ‘On Safe’ to ‘Fire’. Take down for basic cleaning is simple—there are no loose parts. Just remove the rear receiver pin and pivot the upper receiver to open.

The new Chiappa Rhino barrel is aligned with the bottom most chamber which is the key component to Rhino's tame characteristics. The position of the barrel lowers the center of gravity and yields a centerline of the bore more in line with the shooter's arm allowing for the most natural "point ability" while engaging a target. This characteristic also drastically reduces both recoil and muzzle flip which insures subsequent shots to be on target faster than ever before. The reduction of the recoil allows for the use of ultra light alloys to be used in the construction of the Rhino minimizing any adverse effect. The flat sided cylinder design of the Rhino reduces the typical revolver profile allowing greater concealment.With choices from 2"to 6" barrel lengths and sight options, the Rhino is truly a multipurpose handgun capable of reliable defensive duty, scoring ten rings, and taking game. Featuring both double and single action characteristics, the single action is actuated by a hammer cocking device that engages the unexposed hammer to prepare to fire.

title: For Sale:  Zastava M85 7.62x39 bolt action rifle
postcontent:
Selling my Zastava M85 "mini mauser" bolt action hunting rifle. This rifle is chambered in the well-known, widely available, and cost effective 7.62x39 cartridge, making it both extremely versatile and cheap to shoot. I have owned this rifle for about a year or so, bought it brand new. Took it with me down south to hunt feral hogs and here in the NE to hunt whitetail, coyotes, and ground hogs. It's essentially a 30/30 round out of a bolt action rifle, at a fraction of the cost to shoot. Great for someone who already has a 7.62x39 firearm (AK, SKS, etc.) that doesn't want to add a new caliber to their collection. 

Both the bluing and stock on this rifle are deep and rich in color. The Monte Carlo all wood stock is absolutely gorgeous. Overall this piece is in exceptional condition, can hardly tell it has been used. Accuracy is outstanding, have personally taken out 2 deer at around 200 yards and coyote/ground hogs at between 100-200 yards. I haven't had to opportunity to see what it can do past 200-250 yards, but according to the owners manual and various YouTube videos, 400-500 yards with decent ammo is well within its effective range.

Comes with owners/operating manual for the rifle and the retail box for the scope (including users manual and warranty info).
